## 🛠️ Installation & Requirements

To run this software, you must have Python 3.8+ and Google Chrome installed on your system.

### 1. Tesseract OCR Installation (Mandatory)
The system requires the Tesseract OCR engine to read text from images and documents:
1. Download and install the latest version from the [Tesseract OCR Windows Installer](https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki) page.
2. Verify the default installation path: `C:\Program Files\Tesseract-OCR\tesseract.exe`. Update the path in the code if installed elsewhere.

### 2. Dependency Installation
Open a terminal in the project directory and install all required libraries:

```bash
pip install undetected-chromedriver pillow pytesseract pdfplumber pandas openpyxl customtkinter
